OL,3,COfcom investigating GB News programme
OL,4,Cwith Rishi Sunak
OL,6,FOfcom has launched an investigation
OL,7,Finto whether a GB News programme where
OL,8,Fthe prime minister took questions from
OL,9,Fthe public breached impartiality rules.
OL,11,FThe programme saw Rishi Sunak take
OL,12,Fquestions from the public in a live
OL,13,FQ&A in Co Durham on February 12, and
OL,14,Fhas prompted about 500 complaints.
OL,16,FOfcom's rules say when big political
OL,17,Fissues are being discussed
OL,18,Fbroadcasters must feature a wide range
OL,19,Fof significant views.
